text.paragraph:
Antiepileptic drugs (AEDs), including gabapentin, increase the risk of suicidal thoughts or behavior in patients taking these drugs for any indication. Suicidal behavior and ideation have also been reported in patients after discontinuation of gabapentin 
                           [see Warnings and Precautions (5.6)

                           ]. Patients treated with any AED for any indication should be monitored for the emergence or worsening of depression, suicidal thoughts or behavior, and/or any unusual changes in mood or behavior.

The mean bioavailability of gabapentin was reduced by about 20% with concomitant use of an antacid (Maalox
                              ®
                           ) containing magnesium and aluminum hydroxides.  It is recommended that gabapentin be taken at least 2 hours following Maalox administration [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].
